1
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:49,119
Hello, everyone.

2
00:00:49,479 --> 00:00:50,659
I'm Yang Xiaofang.

3
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:51,880
I have something to say.

4
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:53,060
Listen up.

5
00:00:55,039 --> 00:00:56,460
Gossiping aunties of the village,

6
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:57,979
stop worrying about me.

7
00:00:58,859 --> 00:00:59,759
Aunt, Second Aunt,

8
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:00,979
you don't need to fuss over me either.

9
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:03,439
I don't want Qi Xiaowei's bride price.

10
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,280
I'm not marrying him.

11
00:01:06,659 --> 00:01:07,879
I, Yang Xiaofang,

12
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:09,879
don't love Qi Xiaowei anymore.

13
00:01:10,359 --> 00:01:11,840
So I'm not marrying him.

14
00:01:13,659 --> 00:01:15,260
I, Yang Xiaofang,

15
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,879
don't love Qi Xiaowei anymore.

16
00:01:18,519 --> 00:01:21,480
I'm not marrying him.

17
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:24,140
Not marrying him.

18
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:27,560
Yang Xiaofang,

19
00:01:28,239 --> 00:01:29,200
what do you mean?

20
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:30,700
You're pregnant, and you...

21
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,439
You just break up, just like that?

22
00:01:32,459 --> 00:01:33,579
You think this is playing house?

23
00:01:33,739 --> 00:01:34,659
I finally got all the money

24
00:01:34,659 --> 00:01:35,459
sorted out.

25
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:36,040
And what do you do?

26
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,040
You grab a big loudspeaker

27
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,819
and shout at everyone!

28
00:01:37,819 --> 00:01:38,280
Qi Xiaowei,

29
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:39,439
from now on,

30
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:40,599
you don't need to sweet-talk me.

31
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:42,439
And I, Yang Xiaofang, will never

32
00:01:42,439 --> 00:01:43,319
embarrass you again.

33
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:45,480
You go your way, I'll go mine.

34
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:47,000
I'm not joking with you.

35
00:01:47,599 --> 00:01:48,200
I don't love you anymore.

36
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:49,019
We're breaking up.

37
00:01:50,659 --> 00:01:51,379
I don't agree.

38
00:01:52,819 --> 00:01:53,459
Yang Xiaofang,

39
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,239
you're pregnant.

40
00:01:55,579 --> 00:01:56,579
If you don't marry me,

41
00:01:56,659 --> 00:01:57,599
who else are you gonna find?

42
00:01:57,659 --> 00:01:58,540
Who would want you?

43
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:04,840
You hit me?

44
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:06,060
That one's from him.

45
00:02:10,060 --> 00:02:10,740
And this one's from me.

46
00:03:56,659 --> 00:03:57,580
So young,

47
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,479
yet so clueless.

48
00:03:58,539 --> 00:03:59,699
Get up and let me sit.

49
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,400
I paid for my ticket.

50
00:04:01,419 --> 00:04:02,340
So what if you did?

51
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:03,500
Can't you see someone older

52
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,759
standing here? Won't give up your seat?

53
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:05,340
Yeah.

54
00:04:05,860 --> 00:04:06,400
Folks,

55
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:08,340
let's all be considerate.

56
00:04:08,819 --> 00:04:10,879
This extra bus is really packed.

57
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,599
Mid-Autumn is right around the corner.

58
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:13,719
Everyone's rushing home.

59
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:14,159
Exactly.

60
00:04:14,819 --> 00:04:15,879
You've been sitting the whole way.

61
00:04:15,939 --> 00:04:17,000
Get up and let me sit.

62
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,240
Come on, let me sit.

63
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:19,500
Ma'am,

64
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,079
you can have my seat.

65
00:04:23,319 --> 00:04:24,199
Okay, okay, okay.

66
00:04:24,379 --> 00:04:24,959
See that?

67
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:26,420
She's not just young and pretty,

68
00:04:26,579 --> 00:04:27,360
she's also polite.

69
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:28,779
Thank you.

70
00:04:29,699 --> 00:04:31,259
Please, sit down.

71
00:04:31,819 --> 00:04:32,800
Thank you, dear.

72
00:04:35,459 --> 00:04:35,879
Thanks.

73
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:36,920
Ma'am.

74
00:04:37,139 --> 00:04:37,699
She's pregnant.

75
00:04:37,740 --> 00:04:38,800
She's carrying a baby.

76
00:04:38,839 --> 00:04:39,279
Right.

77
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,699
Ma'am, you take my seat.

78
00:04:40,779 --> 00:04:41,800
Let the pregnant lady sit.

79
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,759
It's fine.

80
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:43,920
This lady's older.

81
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,060
Let her have my seat.

82
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,480
You come sit here.

83
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:47,519
No need, you sit.

84
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:50,500
People like her don't deserve a seat.

85
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:51,560
The nerve of her.

86
00:04:57,139 --> 00:04:57,540
My belly...

87
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,620
Did you twist something

88
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:02,740
when you stood up?

89
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:05,180
No, no, I didn't touch you.

90
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,939
You did, I just saw it.

91
00:05:06,939 --> 00:05:07,600
I can vouch for that.

92
00:05:08,019 --> 00:05:08,620
Hey, ma'am,

93
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:10,040
you've got to take responsibility for her.

94
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:10,860
Hurry, take her to the hospital.

95
00:05:10,899 --> 00:05:12,040
Go to the hospital.

96
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:14,000
Ma'am, you're taking me to the hospital.

97
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:14,980
What hospital?

98
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,500
Driver, stop, stop right here!

99
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,480
I'm getting off.

100
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:18,560
I didn't touch you!

101
00:05:18,579 --> 00:05:18,980
I didn't touch you!

102
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,319
Ma'am, she gave up her seat for you!

103
00:05:20,319 --> 00:05:20,779
Don't run!

104
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:21,660
Ma'am!

105
00:05:22,819 --> 00:05:23,399
Don't run!

106
00:05:23,439 --> 00:05:24,899
Our village is still two stops away.

107
00:05:30,139 --> 00:05:30,639
Thank you.

108
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:48,180
Your dad's live-streaming again.

109
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,879
Let's see what nonsense he's up to now.

110
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:53,560
Hey folks!

111
00:05:54,279 --> 00:05:56,600
Welcome to the Hunter Qi Family

112
00:05:57,079 --> 00:05:58,379
livestream channel 5269.

113
00:05:59,079 --> 00:06:02,019
Wild beasts roam these deep mountains.

114
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:04,620
For all you folks stopping by,

115
00:06:04,639 --> 00:06:05,939
don't forget to follow and hit like.

116
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:07,019
Show old Qi some support.

117
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,620
This here is a beast trap.

118
00:06:08,839 --> 00:06:09,519
Wild beasts,

119
00:06:09,819 --> 00:06:11,240
we gotta catch 'em alive, right?

120
00:06:11,939 --> 00:06:12,939
Let you folks see

121
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:15,079
that all our furs are the real deal.

122
00:06:17,579 --> 00:06:18,339
Where'd my trap go?

123
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:19,899
What the heck?

124
00:06:20,819 --> 00:06:22,300
Don't tell me I ran into a real beast.

125
00:06:27,939 --> 00:06:29,740
Who gave you permission

126
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:30,519
to set traps here?

127
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:32,500
Why're you sticking your nose in?

128
00:06:32,899 --> 00:06:33,420
Hey folks,

129
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,779
don't listen to his nonsense.

130
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,160
He's just the village idiot.

131
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:39,360
Why's your dad there too?

132
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:39,879
Folks,

133
00:06:39,980 --> 00:06:40,279
we're done for.

134
00:06:40,579 --> 00:06:41,100
They're gonna start fighting again.

135
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,060
I may be an idiot,

136
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:43,759
but the guy across from me

137
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,480
is a big fat liar.

138
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:46,620
Folks,

139
00:06:47,259 --> 00:06:47,699
take a look,

140
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:50,220
this isn't a deep mountain forest at all.

141
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,879
This is just the little pond

142
00:06:52,259 --> 00:06:53,639
behind our village.

143
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,319
Fancy outfit you got there.

144
00:06:57,939 --> 00:06:59,100
Which tribe you back from?

145
00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:00,279
Yang Fanhu, hand it over.

146
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,259
I can give it to you,

147
00:07:01,579 --> 00:07:02,379
but listen,

148
00:07:03,699 --> 00:07:04,740
making money's fine,

149
00:07:05,399 --> 00:07:06,660
but not money against your conscience.

150
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:08,120
Folks,

151
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:09,540
we're pausing the livestream.

152
00:07:11,339 --> 00:07:12,939
Who the hell do you think you are?

153
00:07:13,759 --> 00:07:14,879
Just a small-time carpenter

154
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:16,519
making pennies a month.

155
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,980
And you dare boss me around?

156
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:18,980
Money, money, money.

157
00:07:19,339 --> 00:07:20,540
You've crawled right into the money hole.

158
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:23,220
With what you're doing,

159
00:07:23,379 --> 00:07:24,220
you'd better watch out.

160
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,699
The Mountain God will come for you.

161
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,779
You think the Mountain God

162
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:28,720
is as bored out of his mind as you?

163
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,199
If there's really a Mountain God,

164
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:31,019
tell him to come out

165
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:32,939
and send a tiger to eat me.

166
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:33,600
Eat me up!

167
00:07:37,420 --> 00:07:38,699
Tiger! Tiger! Tiger!

168
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,660
How come that sound

169
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,699
sounds like a tiger?

170
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:42,879
You're asking for it.

171
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:44,879
The Mountain God's come for you.

172
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:48,980
Don't run!

173
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:50,720
I gotta run!

174
00:07:50,939 --> 00:07:52,199
The Mountain God's gonna eat you!

175
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,480
Hello, hello, hello.

176
00:08:07,639 --> 00:08:09,939
Fellow villagers, hello everyone.

177
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,920
This is Lao San from the village committee.

178
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,079
Here's an urgent announcement.

179
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,160
There's a circus

180
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,279
that had a truck accident in our area.

181
00:08:18,939 --> 00:08:20,300
One of their monkeys escaped.

182
00:08:21,139 --> 00:08:22,019
Let me emphasize,

183
00:08:22,699 --> 00:08:23,439
it's a monkey.

184
00:08:23,939 --> 00:08:24,680
Not a tiger.

185
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,360
Now this monkey

186
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,740
stole a speaker from the circus.

187
00:08:29,519 --> 00:08:30,339
And this speaker

188
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,600
can play sounds of over a dozen animals.

189
00:08:34,059 --> 00:08:35,000
A monkey ran off

190
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:36,000
carrying a speaker?

191
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,980
Did I hear that right?

192
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:37,940
You heard right.

193
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,080
It's just that absurd.

194
00:08:41,019 --> 00:08:42,039
So if anyone hears

195
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,080
sounds of other animals,

196
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:44,440
don't panic.

197
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:46,299
Whatever you do, don't panic.

198
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:50,019
Scared now?

199
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:51,379
Me?

200
00:08:51,620 --> 00:08:52,740
Why would I be scared of a monkey?

201
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:54,480
I mean, Dad.

202
00:08:57,059 --> 00:08:57,960
What have I got to be scared of?

203
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,100
Our two families,

204
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,679
door to door, face to face

205
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:03,179
for over a hundred years, right?

206
00:09:04,860 --> 00:09:05,980
Your dad, my dad,

207
00:09:06,139 --> 00:09:07,379
your grandpa, my grandpa.

208
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,740
We're all long-standing family friends.

209
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:11,899
Long-standing? More like a family feud.

210
00:09:14,259 --> 00:09:14,820
Qiu Mei.

211
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:16,600
Qiu Mei!

212
00:09:18,159 --> 00:09:19,600
How did you store these hides?

213
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,059
You can't stack them together.

214
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:21,960
They're all damp now.

215
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:23,399
I know, I know.

216
00:09:24,059 --> 00:09:25,139
How many times have I told you?

217
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:28,980
Look at you, you coward.

218
00:09:29,539 --> 00:09:30,759
Did the tiger scare the piss out of you?

219
00:10:01,659 --> 00:10:02,679
My dad and your dad

220
00:10:02,779 --> 00:10:04,620
have been sworn enemies for most of their lives.

221
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,240
Ever since our grandpas fought over herbs,

222
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,480
they've been butting heads

223
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,960
over every little petty thing.

224
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,059
Keep shaking and all the fur will fall off.

225
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:31,220
It's time.

226
00:10:31,220 --> 00:10:32,139
Go pick up your son.

227
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:33,179
Quit rushing me.

228
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:34,379
Let that little brat wait.

229
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:37,659
No matter if our families

230
00:10:37,659 --> 00:10:38,919
are called enemies by others

231
00:10:39,259 --> 00:10:40,980
or old friends as you stubbornly claim.

232
00:10:41,419 --> 00:10:42,860
As long as we're on the same page,

233
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,620
we can definitely be together

234
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:46,100
openly and rightfully.

235
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:50,000
And if that still doesn't work?

236
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:51,720
If it still doesn't work,

237
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:54,000
we'll have to bring Grandma into it.

238
00:10:55,559 --> 00:10:56,340
Granny,

239
00:10:57,039 --> 00:10:58,720
these are our own farm eggs.

240
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,659
Cut me a deal, I'll buy more.

241
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:05,500
Who buys anything without haggling?

242
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,620
As a seller,

243
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,779
if you're too stubborn,

244
00:11:07,779 --> 00:11:08,559
you won't sell anything.

245
00:11:08,759 --> 00:11:10,279
Are these really free-range eggs?

246
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:11,960
They're way too clean.

247
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,179
Not even a speck of chicken poop.

248
00:11:14,679 --> 00:11:16,700
I'm recording. Ten times refund for fakes.

249
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:19,480
Why is there a camera?

250
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,159
Customers who argue,

251
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,860
take the eggs home,

252
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,159
then swap them out,

253
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:27,019
I need to get some evidence

254
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,840
so the market management

255
00:11:29,059 --> 00:11:30,100
can back me up.

256
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:31,220
Are egg sellers these days

257
00:11:31,220 --> 00:11:32,259
really this cutthroat?

258
00:11:38,159 --> 00:11:38,539
Hello?

259
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:39,679
Yan'er.

260
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:40,799
Mom.

261
00:11:41,059 --> 00:11:42,840
Mid-Autumn Festival is right around the corner.

262
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,340
When are you coming home?

263
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:45,799
I'll have your brother pick you up.

264
00:11:46,379 --> 00:11:46,779
Mom,

265
00:11:47,019 --> 00:11:49,039
I'm going to the Maldives with Dou Cheng.

266
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:50,500
The Mal-what?

267
00:11:50,879 --> 00:11:51,799
The Maldives.

268
00:11:52,059 --> 00:11:53,419
Dou Cheng booked a Presidential Suite.

269
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:55,200
I won't be coming back this year.

270
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:57,179
Not coming home for Mid-Autumn?

271
00:11:57,379 --> 00:11:58,799
I was hoping you'd bring

272
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,559
Dou Cheng back with you.

273
00:12:00,779 --> 00:12:01,139
Mom,

274
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:02,399
I've got something to do,

275
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:03,659
I'll talk to you later.

276
00:12:10,379 --> 00:12:11,399
Hung up faster than I did.

277
00:12:15,299 --> 00:12:16,759
I thought after the divorce,

278
00:12:17,019 --> 00:12:18,779
you wouldn't care if I lived or died.

279
00:12:19,159 --> 00:12:20,000
Don't be silly.

280
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:21,960
You're here taking care of your ex-wife.

281
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,340
Won't your girlfriend get mad?

282
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:25,519
At our age, why fuss over that?

283
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,039
I've got time to look after you.

284
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:30,820
But what about your Aunt?

285
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:32,340
Aunt?

286
00:12:32,340 --> 00:12:33,740
She's busy with her second spring.

287
00:12:35,279 --> 00:12:35,600
Yan'er.

288
00:12:36,299 --> 00:12:36,720
I'm here.

289
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:38,840
And this is?

290
00:12:39,139 --> 00:12:39,940
I'm Fanyan.

291
00:12:41,139 --> 00:12:43,259
Dou said you're having surgery.

292
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:44,720
What terrible timing.

293
00:12:45,059 --> 00:12:46,059
The two of us are about to leave

294
00:12:46,059 --> 00:12:47,100
for a trip to the Maldives.

295
00:12:47,139 --> 00:12:48,700
So we came by today to see you.

296
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,440
Going where?

297
00:12:50,460 --> 00:12:51,360
You didn't know either?

298
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:52,860
Dou wanted

299
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:54,720
to surprise me.

300
00:12:54,860 --> 00:12:56,919
Just got the hotel confirmation.

301
00:12:57,259 --> 00:12:58,100
Why did you go and book

302
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,039
the Honeymoon Suite?

303
00:13:00,059 --> 00:13:01,100
Unbelievable. Come on, come on.

304
00:13:01,299 --> 00:13:02,700
Dou has no idea how to care for anyone.

305
00:13:02,799 --> 00:13:03,440
Let me, let me.

306
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,620
Um, I'll just call you sis.

307
00:13:06,059 --> 00:13:06,860
Do you want me

308
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,179
to prop this up a bit for you?

309
00:13:08,340 --> 00:13:09,340
No need, it's fine like this.

310
00:13:10,139 --> 00:13:11,539
You haven't eaten. Let me feed you.

311
00:13:11,799 --> 00:13:13,440
Just had some. Dou fed me.

312
00:13:15,559 --> 00:13:17,120
Come on, you, you sit down.

313
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,779
Have some fruit. It's already peeled.

314
00:13:18,919 --> 00:13:19,899
I bought a whole lot too.

315
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:20,419
Come on, come on.

316
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,759
I can't eat fruit right now.

317
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:24,480
Can't eat it, huh?

318
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,759
Then you have some.

319
00:13:26,899 --> 00:13:28,039
My mouth's parched from talking.

320
00:13:28,159 --> 00:13:28,759
Come on, come on.

321
00:13:34,159 --> 00:13:35,500
I don't like sour stuff either.

322
00:13:37,139 --> 00:13:37,960
What about your Second Aunt?

323
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:40,840
Second Aunt has money and free time,

324
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,799
living the good life.

325
00:13:46,559 --> 00:13:47,440
Hello, Mom.

326
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:48,379
Fanmei.

327
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:49,980
When are you coming home?

328
00:13:50,139 --> 00:13:51,620
I'll have your brother pick you up.

329
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:53,200
Mom, I'm really too busy.

330
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:53,940
I can't come back.

331
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:55,700
I'll visit when I have time,

332
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:56,220
okay?

333
00:14:00,379 --> 00:14:01,120
I gotta go now.

334
00:14:06,379 --> 00:14:06,779
Stop right there!

335
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,480
That's what my dad owes.

336
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:10,340
Why come after us?

337
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,179
Stop!

338
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,039
I'm not the one who owes that money.

339
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,039
Why are you following me?

340
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,419
Go, go find the actual debtor!

341
00:14:23,460 --> 00:14:24,259
Ma'am.

342
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,639
Please put in a word with Mr. Qian.

343
00:14:27,159 --> 00:14:28,679
I'm really having a tough time.

344
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,559
Just a hundred grand or so.

345
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,200
Pay me back, please.

346
00:14:33,559 --> 00:14:33,980
Mom.

347
00:14:34,059 --> 00:14:35,500
I'm tired from crying, I want bubble tea.

348
00:14:36,059 --> 00:14:36,759
All you do is drink.

349
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,240
Run!

350
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:47,019
Mom!

351
00:14:47,179 --> 00:14:47,679
Hello?

352
00:14:48,639 --> 00:14:49,419
Fan Zhu.

353
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:52,179
Are you busy for Mid-Autumn too?

354
00:14:52,220 --> 00:14:53,100
Not coming home?

355
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,159
Can't make it. Got a pitch to do.

356
00:14:55,639 --> 00:14:57,240
When I'm free, I'll come visit you.

357
00:14:57,679 --> 00:14:58,419
End of the year, I'd guess.

358
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,860
As for Uncle...

359
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:00,419
Xiaorou, hold on a sec.

360
00:15:00,419 --> 00:15:01,179
Mom, I gotta go.

361
00:15:01,179 --> 00:15:01,960
Xiaorou! Xiaorou!

362
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,000
Better take care of yourself first.

363
00:15:05,799 --> 00:15:07,639
Young people these days...

364
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,240
they're all under so much stress.

365
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,299
But have nowhere to let it out.

366
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:13,600
This...

367
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:16,080
is our new launch,

368
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:16,940
an interactive segment.

369
00:15:17,259 --> 00:15:19,500
It lets all the working folks

370
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:22,220
release all their frustration and anger,

371
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,620
let it all out.

372
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,120
This standee...

373
00:15:28,379 --> 00:15:29,720
It's not modeled after me, is it?

374
00:15:33,539 --> 00:15:35,759
No, boss. It's symbolic.

375
00:15:36,059 --> 00:15:36,399
Look.

376
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:37,879
See, I stand here. Look.

377
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:38,879
Same thing.

378
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:39,840
Symbolic.

379
00:15:40,820 --> 00:15:41,519
Symbolic.

380
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:44,240
Neither coincidence nor accident.

381
00:15:44,259 --> 00:15:44,779
No...

382
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:46,779
Starting tomorrow,

383
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,120
don't bother coming in.

384
00:15:48,299 --> 00:15:49,340
You're fired.

385
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:50,899
Busy, busy, busy.

386
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,940
No time to even talk to your mom.

387
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:54,100
Come home or don't, whatever.

388
00:15:58,600 --> 00:15:59,940
Your kid isn't coming home for Mid-Autumn?

389
00:16:00,299 --> 00:16:00,820
Auntie.

390
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:02,200
How many kids do you have?

391
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:02,899
Four.

392
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,220
All doing well.

393
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:05,919
What is it?

394
00:16:06,919 --> 00:16:07,700
Kids these days...

395
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:08,620
So ungrateful.

396
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,320
That's pricey, Auntie.

397
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,620
I'll take a bunch.

398
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,240
Ten yuan a pound.

399
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,179
Wasn't it five? Why the hike?

400
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,559
Keep talking and I'll raise it more.

401
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:24,419
Hello?

402
00:16:26,539 --> 00:16:27,460
Xiaofang's back!

403
00:16:27,879 --> 00:16:29,320
Okay, I'm heading back now.

404
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,039
Come, come, come.

405
00:16:30,059 --> 00:16:30,419
You.

406
00:16:31,759 --> 00:16:32,460
How much do you want?

407
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,059
Four yuan a pound.

408
00:16:34,399 --> 00:16:34,899
Here.

409
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:35,679
Weigh it.

410
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:46,700
Save energy, cut emissions.

411
00:16:47,059 --> 00:16:48,659
Protect the environment.

412
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,700
Protect the environment.

413
00:16:51,059 --> 00:16:52,860
Save energy, cut emissions.

414
00:16:54,519 --> 00:16:55,720
Your junker is the least eco-friendly.

415
00:17:04,279 --> 00:17:07,000
Fairy Peak's air feels so much better.

416
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:16,380
We're already here.

417
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:18,119
Stop looking so gloomy.

418
00:17:19,259 --> 00:17:19,779
Give me a smile.

419
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,259
Worst case, I'll elope with you.

420
00:17:25,539 --> 00:17:26,220
Okay.

421
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:27,940
If it comes to it,

422
00:17:28,059 --> 00:17:28,900
we'll fight them head on.

423
00:17:29,099 --> 00:17:29,480
Yeah.

424
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,759
Now that's my warrior.

425
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:32,539
Anyone dares stop us,

426
00:17:32,980 --> 00:17:34,299
we'll fight them head on.

427
00:17:34,380 --> 00:17:34,740
Bring it on!

428
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,700
Once we hold hands,

429
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,380
it's forever.

430
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,880
Short by a year, a month,

431
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:43,000
none of that counts as forever.

432
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:43,640
Xiaofang.

433
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:44,940
Dad.

434
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:06,579
Dad, Dad!

435
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:07,740
My luggage is still over there.

436
00:18:07,980 --> 00:18:08,359
Look.

437
00:18:22,859 --> 00:18:23,299
Uncle Yang.

438
00:18:42,759 --> 00:18:44,220
What the hell? Neither male nor female.

439
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:47,240
Me? Dad.

440
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,019
You...

441
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:50,279
No, wait.

442
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:51,799
No, wait.

443
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:52,920
You...

444
00:18:53,140 --> 00:18:53,980
What kind of hairstyle is this?

445
00:18:54,380 --> 00:18:56,279
You little punk, you trying to be an idol?

446
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,579
You wanna be an idol?

447
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:58,579
What is this you've grown?

448
00:18:59,119 --> 00:19:00,079
Looking like a total hooligan.

449
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,440
This your luggage?

450
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:02,759
Let's go.

451
00:19:08,759 --> 00:19:09,380
Don't I look handsome?

452
00:19:09,519 --> 00:19:10,019
Come on, let's go.

453
00:19:10,519 --> 00:19:11,460
Handsome my ass!

454
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:22,420
You got fat.

455
00:19:25,299 --> 00:19:26,180
A bit chubby is a good thing.

456
00:19:37,019 --> 00:19:38,460
Yang Fanhu, you and your crappy car!

457
00:19:38,619 --> 00:19:39,259
Driving so damn slow!

458
00:19:39,339 --> 00:19:39,859
You crawling?

459
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:44,900
You're on a mountain road!

460
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:45,819
Why the hell are you racing?

461
00:19:46,039 --> 00:19:46,599
No manners at all!

462
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:47,359
Get lost!

463
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:49,339
If you don't like it, get out and walk!

464
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:52,400
Dad.

465
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,500
Xiaowei and I...

466
00:19:57,359 --> 00:19:57,859
No way.

467
00:19:59,359 --> 00:20:00,259
Why not?

468
00:20:02,799 --> 00:20:04,019
His grandpa's a poacher.

469
00:20:04,359 --> 00:20:05,720
His dad sells fake goods.

470
00:20:06,339 --> 00:20:07,220
A whole family of con artists.

471
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,960
But Xiaowei's not part of that.

472
00:20:09,279 --> 00:20:10,279
He's into the arts.

473
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:13,579
You're Yang Fanhu's daughter!

474
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,259
You reckless little thing!

475
00:20:15,259 --> 00:20:16,619
Why are you throwing yourself at them?

476
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,640
Sure, Yang Fanhu did time,

477
00:20:19,859 --> 00:20:20,880
but Xiaofang's a good person.

478
00:20:21,579 --> 00:20:23,140
Just like Grandpa poached, but you only sell

479
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:23,940
fake furs.

480
00:20:24,099 --> 00:20:24,980
You don't harm animals.

481
00:20:25,119 --> 00:20:27,059
Character isn't something you inherit.

482
00:20:27,680 --> 00:20:29,119
You idiot!

483
00:20:29,359 --> 00:20:30,579
Long hair, short on brains!

484
00:20:30,579 --> 00:20:31,500
How dare you talk back to me!

485
00:20:31,579 --> 00:20:32,640
Talk back to me, will you!

486
00:20:32,799 --> 00:20:34,000
How many days since you washed this hair?

487
00:20:34,119 --> 00:20:34,619
How many days?

488
00:20:34,619 --> 00:20:35,079
Stop hitting me!

489
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:36,700
I'm gonna be a dad! Stop hitting me!

490
00:20:37,079 --> 00:20:37,460
What?

491
00:20:42,579 --> 00:20:43,460
Yang Xiaofang's pregnant.

492
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,339
It's my kid.

493
00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:50,440
Hey, what're you doing? Is this necessary?

494
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,420
Is this necessary?

495
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,440
Is this necessary?

496
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:54,779
Is this necessary?

497
00:20:54,940 --> 00:20:55,440
Hey, what are you looking for?

498
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,460
You messed with the Yang family?

499
00:20:56,460 --> 00:20:56,940
What are you looking for?

500
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,480
You have a death wish!

501
00:21:03,359 --> 00:21:04,099
Stop right there!

502
00:21:05,339 --> 00:21:06,759
You... you...

503
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:07,500
Who?

504
00:21:08,799 --> 00:21:10,039
Why on earth did you mess with the Yangs?

505
00:21:10,039 --> 00:21:10,920
Dad, stop the car!

506
00:21:11,119 --> 00:21:11,819
Stop right there!

507
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:13,660
Dad!

508
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:14,059
Stop!

509
00:21:14,799 --> 00:21:15,460
Xiaowei!

510
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:17,319
Xiaowei!

511
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:18,619
You head back first.

512
00:21:20,079 --> 00:21:20,579
Dad.

513
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,460
Xiaowei and I are together.

514
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:31,420
I'm pregnant.

515
00:21:44,759 --> 00:21:45,319
So...

516
00:21:52,099 --> 00:21:53,079
You're gonna be a grandpa.

517
00:22:03,619 --> 00:22:04,839
You're here.

518
00:22:05,980 --> 00:22:06,279
Okay.

519
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:07,519
You're here.

520
00:22:13,660 --> 00:22:14,400
Xiaofang.

521
00:22:14,619 --> 00:22:15,019
Grandma.

522
00:22:15,019 --> 00:22:16,500
Here's some soy milk.

523
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,160
Careful, it's hot.

524
00:22:19,539 --> 00:22:20,160
Slow down, it's hot.

525
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:20,720
So hot, so hot!

526
00:22:25,579 --> 00:22:27,200
Hot, hot, hot!

527
00:22:27,599 --> 00:22:28,779
But it's so good.

528
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:30,700
Outside our factory,

529
00:22:30,859 --> 00:22:31,900
there's a soy milk vendor too.

530
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,279
But theirs is watery as heck.

531
00:22:35,140 --> 00:22:36,380
Nothing beats homemade.

532
00:22:38,460 --> 00:22:39,099
Now that you're back,

533
00:22:39,259 --> 00:22:40,440
eat all you want.

534
00:22:40,839 --> 00:22:41,720
Whatever you want,

535
00:22:41,980 --> 00:22:42,700
just tell Grandma.

536
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:44,019
I'll make it for you.

537
00:22:44,819 --> 00:22:46,059
There's so much I want to eat.

538
00:22:46,279 --> 00:22:47,819
I want your dry-fried pork intestines,

539
00:22:48,039 --> 00:22:48,660
crispy meatballs,

540
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:49,759
and your stewed pig's trotters.

541
00:22:51,579 --> 00:22:52,119
But then...

542
00:22:53,460 --> 00:22:54,539
if I eat too much,

543
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:55,700
won't I get fat and...

544
00:22:56,019 --> 00:22:57,299
have a hard time giving birth?

545
00:22:58,339 --> 00:23:00,019
Don't worry.

546
00:23:00,359 --> 00:23:02,279
You, your aunts,

547
00:23:02,460 --> 00:23:03,140
you all take after me.

548
00:23:03,759 --> 00:23:05,380
When I was pregnant, I didn't gain weight.

549
00:23:05,380 --> 00:23:06,680
Didn't even show.

550
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:08,480
Look at your belly.

551
00:23:08,799 --> 00:23:10,119
If you don't look closely,

552
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:11,480
you can't even tell.

553
00:23:15,599 --> 00:23:17,059
Why didn't you tell

554
00:23:17,059 --> 00:23:18,359
the family sooner?

555
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:20,299
Seeing is believing, right?

556
00:23:20,299 --> 00:23:22,220
I wanted you to see it in person.

557
00:23:22,220 --> 00:23:23,240
You can't explain it over the phone.

558
00:23:24,460 --> 00:23:25,779
Seeing is believing, my foot.

559
00:23:26,319 --> 00:23:28,039
Look how mad your dad is.

560
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:30,000
His face is all dark.

561
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:33,240
His face is always dark.

562
00:23:35,660 --> 00:23:37,319
Because you were coming back,

563
00:23:37,599 --> 00:23:39,400
your dad cleaned this whole house

564
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,539
from top to bottom.

565
00:23:41,079 --> 00:23:43,519
He just can't wrap his head around it.

566
00:23:43,980 --> 00:23:45,299
You need to understand him.

567
00:23:49,099 --> 00:23:50,759
I know Dad's good to me.

568
00:23:52,859 --> 00:23:53,900
But Grandma,

569
00:23:55,059 --> 00:23:55,740
but...

570
00:23:57,700 --> 00:23:59,660
Xiaowei and I already talked it over.

571
00:24:01,420 --> 00:24:02,359
What did you decide?

572
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:05,819
We're going all in.

573
00:24:10,420 --> 00:24:10,900
Good.

574
00:24:11,220 --> 00:24:12,539
Having a baby,

575
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,220
what's the big deal?

576
00:24:15,079 --> 00:24:16,559
Just take good care of yourself.

577
00:24:16,759 --> 00:24:17,559
Don't think about anything else.

578
00:24:19,759 --> 00:24:20,480
Grandma, you're my

579
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:21,500
strongest support.

580
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,559
With you here, I'm not afraid of anything.

581
00:24:23,980 --> 00:24:24,779
Don't worry.

582
00:24:25,539 --> 00:24:26,619
Xiaowei will definitely

583
00:24:26,619 --> 00:24:27,279
sort things out.

584
00:24:28,460 --> 00:24:28,880
Good.

585
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:30,680
I brought you a gift.

586
00:24:31,619 --> 00:24:32,059
It's just...

587
00:24:32,059 --> 00:24:33,539
Your knees always hurt, right?

588
00:24:34,039 --> 00:24:34,640
Try this.

589
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,240
It's got massage and heat functions.

590
00:24:38,279 --> 00:24:39,259
There are different settings.

591
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,240
It feels great.

592
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,819
I got Dad a gift too.

593
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:52,339
You're so sweet.

594
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,039
But he's ignoring me now,

595
00:24:54,039 --> 00:24:54,960
so I won't give it to him.

596
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:56,619
When he talks to me, then I'll give it.

597
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:57,980
Right.

598
00:24:58,539 --> 00:25:00,180
Let him cool off on his own.

599
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:02,440
Look.

600
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:06,279
Doesn't this tiger look like Dad?

601
00:25:07,059 --> 00:25:08,759
Cover the "king" mark on its forehead,

602
00:25:08,759 --> 00:25:09,920
and it looks like a kitten.

603
00:25:09,980 --> 00:25:13,299
Meow, meow, meow.

604
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:26,880
Look, just look at that.

605
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:28,579
Is he really chopping firewood?

606
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:29,859
No, he wants to chop you up!

607
00:25:31,579 --> 00:25:33,440
I'll give Xiaofang an Honorable marriage.

608
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:34,319
How could he chop me?

609
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:35,960
Honorable marriage, my foot!

610
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:37,640
If you're so tough, marry her yourself.

611
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,079
Don't ask me for a single cent.

612
00:25:40,019 --> 00:25:40,539
You're such a...

613
00:25:41,079 --> 00:25:41,700
Bully at home!

614
00:25:42,099 --> 00:25:42,660
If you've got guts,

615
00:25:42,799 --> 00:25:44,059
go take on Yang Fanhu.

616
00:25:44,759 --> 00:25:45,640
You don't even dare step outside

617
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:46,839
just to chop firewood.

618
00:25:46,839 --> 00:25:47,380
Who says I don't dare?

619
00:25:49,599 --> 00:25:50,160
Son,

620
00:25:50,599 --> 00:25:54,039
your hair looks awful.

621
00:25:54,359 --> 00:25:54,759
Haiyun,

622
00:25:55,259 --> 00:25:55,819
go get the clippers.

623
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:56,759
Me? Me?

624
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:57,619
Wait, what are you doing?

625
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:58,539
What are you doing?

626
00:25:59,039 --> 00:25:59,660
You're back in the village,

627
00:25:59,799 --> 00:26:00,960
sporting that mop of long hair.

628
00:26:01,180 --> 00:26:01,980
Trying to embarrass me on purpose?

629
00:26:02,339 --> 00:26:02,759
Shave it off.

630
00:26:04,299 --> 00:26:04,880
I won't.

631
00:26:05,539 --> 00:26:06,599
My head can roll, my blood can spill,

632
00:26:06,599 --> 00:26:07,500
but my hair stays intact.

633
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:14,640
Oh, Sanniang,

634
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,680
these young folks nowadays,

635
00:26:16,839 --> 00:26:17,720
they've really got some nerve.

636
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,319
She came back with a big belly!

637
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,059
Couldn't control his wife, she ran off.

638
00:26:22,519 --> 00:26:23,819
Now he can't control his daughter either.

639
00:26:24,339 --> 00:26:26,220
Who knows whose bastard child she's carrying.

640
00:26:29,059 --> 00:26:30,819
The Yangs are really a disgrace.

641
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:35,519
Hey, Yang,

642
00:26:35,819 --> 00:26:36,539
chopping firewood, huh?

643
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,700
Heard you're about to be a grandpa.

644
00:26:38,980 --> 00:26:39,920
Congratulations, congratulations!

645
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,559
We haven't even attended

646
00:26:41,559 --> 00:26:42,559
Xiaofang's wedding yet.

647
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,079
Are the wedding and the baby's one-month party

648
00:26:44,099 --> 00:26:44,960
going to be held together?

649
00:26:45,140 --> 00:26:46,319
We'll pay double.

650
00:26:46,779 --> 00:26:47,119
Right.

651
00:26:47,599 --> 00:26:48,539
We'll give two gifts.

652
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:51,700
I can't quite control my strength here.

653
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:54,039
Watch out, something might fly off.

654
00:26:54,039 --> 00:26:54,740
Not the wood,

655
00:26:55,099 --> 00:26:56,019
but the axe.

656
00:26:57,059 --> 00:26:58,740
Whoever it hits is out of luck.

657
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:01,400
Don't get blood all over yourself.

658
00:27:01,799 --> 00:27:02,819
Getting worked up already?

659
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:56,640
Oh my God!

660
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,720
Yang Fanhu's coming to hack someone!

661
00:27:59,539 --> 00:28:00,779
Where? Where is he?

662
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:08,319
Is there no law anymore?

663
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:09,940
You dare? Come on then!

664
00:28:10,019 --> 00:28:10,980
Let's see if you dare swing that!

665
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,019
Your son's got such a dumb head,

666
00:28:14,019 --> 00:28:15,099
he takes right after you!

667
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,420
You think Yang Fanhu's someone to mess with?

668
00:28:16,759 --> 00:28:17,359
When he's fuming mad,

669
00:28:17,359 --> 00:28:18,160
there's nothing he won't do!

670
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:19,799
Back when his wife cheated on him,

671
00:28:19,799 --> 00:28:20,960
he nearly beat the guy to death!

672
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,400
I was standing right there watching!

673
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:24,779
Qi Xiaowei, you fool!

674
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:26,819
You dared to mess with his daughter?

675
00:28:27,319 --> 00:28:28,380
Got a death wish or something?

676
00:28:28,779 --> 00:28:30,140
We... we didn't do anything wrong!

677
00:28:31,539 --> 00:28:32,680
We're in a serious relationship!

678
00:28:32,819 --> 00:28:33,940
You already knocked her up!

679
00:28:34,099 --> 00:28:35,099
Serious, my ass!

680
00:28:35,460 --> 00:28:36,980
He's already at the middle of the bridge!

681
00:28:37,779 --> 00:28:38,900
Hurry, block the door with something!

682
00:28:39,140 --> 00:28:39,500
Got it!

683
00:28:41,759 --> 00:28:42,640
She's not even married in yet,

684
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:44,460
and it looks like they're about to brawl!

685
00:28:44,819 --> 00:28:46,500
These Butterfly Lovers of ours...

686
00:28:47,039 --> 00:28:47,759
These two families

687
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:49,000
never got along in the first place.

688
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,759
But of all things, their kids

689
00:28:50,759 --> 00:28:51,480
went and hooked up!

690
00:28:51,900 --> 00:28:53,559
So this whole mess? Real tricky now.

691
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,400
Why did he stop moving?

692
00:28:56,660 --> 00:28:57,180
Where? Where is he?

693
00:29:09,299 --> 00:29:09,940
Uncle.

694
00:29:13,019 --> 00:29:14,279
Is Xiaofang back, Uncle?

695
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:17,079
Let's go see her then.

696
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:18,000
Let's go.

697
00:29:18,059 --> 00:29:18,299
Come on.

698
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:19,160
Bye, Uncle.

699
00:29:21,900 --> 00:29:23,920
Xiaofang! Xiaofang!

700
00:29:25,859 --> 00:29:28,299
Come, let's go find Auntie Xiaofang.

701
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:29,059
Okay?

702
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:31,380
Careful.

703
00:29:31,380 --> 00:29:31,900
You're here!

704
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:32,920
You're here!

705
00:29:33,299 --> 00:29:35,180
I missed you so much, Xiaofang.

706
00:29:35,819 --> 00:29:37,599
You didn't even come down to greet us.

707
00:29:37,599 --> 00:29:38,420
Seriously.

708
00:29:38,460 --> 00:29:39,559
Putting on airs, huh?

709
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:39,960
Come.

710
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:41,079
Take a look.

711
00:29:41,339 --> 00:29:41,980
Look at her belly.

712
00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:42,839
Oh my god.

713
00:29:43,660 --> 00:29:45,420
You're barely showing at all.

714
00:29:45,900 --> 00:29:46,740
When I was pregnant,

715
00:29:46,740 --> 00:29:47,700
my belly was huge.

716
00:29:48,460 --> 00:29:49,339
How does it feel?

717
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:50,359
Take a guess.

718
00:29:50,420 --> 00:29:51,740
There's a little life in there.

719
00:29:51,740 --> 00:29:52,799
Let me touch for luck.

720
00:30:02,579 --> 00:30:04,400
Fanyan, put yourself in my shoes.

721
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,079
If I don't stop her,

722
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,099
she'll call my son back home.

723
00:30:08,220 --> 00:30:09,119
If he comes back,

724
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:10,220
it'll mess up his studies,

725
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:12,220
and the flight alone costs tens of thousands.

726
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,200
I'm just trying to save money.

727
00:30:14,299 --> 00:30:15,460
You can't save that money.

728
00:30:16,319 --> 00:30:17,299
You already booked the flights.

729
00:30:17,759 --> 00:30:18,859
The hotel's already confirmed.

730
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,579
I already cancelled it.

731
00:30:21,559 --> 00:30:22,619
Something this big,

732
00:30:23,180 --> 00:30:23,819
why didn't you

733
00:30:23,819 --> 00:30:24,779
discuss it with me first?

734
00:30:24,839 --> 00:30:26,019
You've always been reasonable.

735
00:30:26,079 --> 00:30:27,180
Cut it out with the

736
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:27,859
crocodile tears.

737
00:30:28,740 --> 00:30:30,099
I already told my mom

738
00:30:30,259 --> 00:30:31,660
I was going to the Maldives with you.

739
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:32,640
Now how am I supposed

740
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:33,519
to face my family?

741
00:30:34,759 --> 00:30:36,420
Just tell your mom you're not going.

742
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:38,380
You think I'm like you?

743
00:30:38,500 --> 00:30:39,279
Going back on your word.

744
00:30:40,940 --> 00:30:41,460
Hello?

745
00:30:41,980 --> 00:30:42,440
Brother.

746
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,140
Go ahead, what is it?

747
00:30:46,880 --> 00:30:47,720
Xiaofang...

748
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:49,539
What about Xiaofang?

749
00:30:52,299 --> 00:30:53,140
She's pregnant.

750
00:30:53,980 --> 00:30:55,400
Xiaofang is pregnant.

751
00:30:56,140 --> 00:30:56,500
This...

752
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:58,940
Drawing the curtains in broad daylight,

753
00:30:59,539 --> 00:31:00,740
not even daring to fart out loud.

754
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:03,000
How can we live like this?

755
00:31:03,819 --> 00:31:04,279
Oh mama.

756
00:31:04,359 --> 00:31:05,900
Keep your voice down, will you?

757
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,660
You didn't used to be like this, Meimei.

758
00:31:09,579 --> 00:31:10,779
Well, you didn't used to be in debt either.

759
00:31:12,839 --> 00:31:13,460
Right, right, right.

760
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:14,619
Then let's do this,

761
00:31:15,279 --> 00:31:16,220
take our son

762
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:17,579
back to your parents' place to lay low.

763
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:18,839
I'll handle things here.

764
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:19,920
How can I go back?

765
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:21,579
I don't have a single cent.

766
00:31:22,079 --> 00:31:23,279
You want me to go back and embarrass myself?

767
00:31:23,460 --> 00:31:24,160
I'll figure something out.

768
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:24,920
Okay?

769
00:31:32,420 --> 00:31:32,859
Fan Mei.

770
00:31:33,319 --> 00:31:33,759
What is it?

771
00:31:34,420 --> 00:31:35,640
Xiaofang is pregnant before marriage.

772
00:31:35,779 --> 00:31:36,819
It's that Qi family boy's.

773
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:37,619
What?

774
00:31:38,599 --> 00:31:39,900
Our brother didn't stab anyone, did he?

775
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:45,900
Looks like reason

776
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:47,559
won out over that reckless outlaw in him.

777
00:32:08,980 --> 00:32:09,559
Where are you going?

778
00:32:20,259 --> 00:32:21,319
I'm going to the shop.

779
00:32:35,319 --> 00:32:37,279
It's dark. I'll go with you.

780
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,880
Fine, I'm going to meet Xiaowei.

781
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,259
You don't need to come.

782
00:32:46,579 --> 00:32:48,660
Whatever it is, tell him to come here.

783
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:49,519
No, if you act like this,

784
00:32:49,519 --> 00:32:50,519
how would he dare come?

785
00:32:50,779 --> 00:32:52,599
He doesn't even have the guts

786
00:32:53,619 --> 00:32:55,019
to marry my daughter!

787
00:33:01,460 --> 00:33:02,500
Alright.

788
00:33:02,700 --> 00:33:04,099
Then I won't go.

789
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,099
Okay?

790
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:09,559
Alright.

791
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:10,960
I'm going back to sleep.

792
00:33:11,059 --> 00:33:11,940
You get some sleep early too.

793
00:33:31,359 --> 00:33:33,259
Xiaowei, I can't get out.

794
00:33:33,359 --> 00:33:34,680
Come over here if you wanna talk.

795
00:33:35,759 --> 00:33:36,440
Xiaofang.

796
00:33:37,180 --> 00:33:37,640
Xiaofang.

797
00:33:43,500 --> 00:33:44,279
Are you okay?

798
00:33:52,299 --> 00:33:54,000
I'm fine. I saw it coming.

799
00:33:54,299 --> 00:33:55,099
What about your family?

800
00:33:57,220 --> 00:33:58,299
My parents chewed me out.

801
00:33:59,019 --> 00:34:00,640
But why does everyone else get to judge me?

802
00:34:00,859 --> 00:34:02,339
Their mouths belong to them.

803
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:03,940
We can't stop them from talking.

804
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,319
No way, I'm the man here.

805
00:34:06,319 --> 00:34:06,779
I've gotta do something.

806
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:09,119
Is this a guy-girl thing now?

807
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:13,920
Big cities are better after all.

808
00:34:14,260 --> 00:34:15,400
Nobody knows us here.

809
00:34:17,579 --> 00:34:19,039
We'll have to face it sooner or later.

810
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:21,199
But as long as we stick together,

811
00:34:21,199 --> 00:34:22,199
we've got nothing to fear.

812
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:24,460
Everything will be just fine.

813
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:25,519
Whatever you say.

814
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:27,780
It's the sweet and bitter of life.

815
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:28,760
We can't have all the sweetness

816
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:29,920
all to ourselves.

817
00:34:30,260 --> 00:34:30,619
Right.

818
00:34:31,099 --> 00:34:32,739
But I'm feeling pretty sweet right now.

819
00:34:35,599 --> 00:34:36,119
Give me a kiss.

820
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:39,400
Come on, kiss me.

821
00:34:46,219 --> 00:34:46,940
Why're you running off?

822
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,059
Why'd you scare him?

823
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:06,719
Did I scare him?

824
00:35:35,179 --> 00:35:35,679
What are you screaming for?

825
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:37,280
Did I scare you?

826
00:35:44,719 --> 00:35:45,219
Eighty-six.

827
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,480
Let me check these pears, looks like...

828
00:35:51,719 --> 00:35:52,440
Look, sis.

829
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:53,659
This one's not bad.

830
00:35:53,780 --> 00:35:54,659
It doesn't look good though.

831
00:35:54,679 --> 00:35:55,300
Let me take out a few.

832
00:35:56,300 --> 00:35:56,679
I don't want them.

833
00:35:57,980 --> 00:35:58,900
That's about right, enough.

834
00:35:59,619 --> 00:36:00,199
How much now?

835
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:01,380
Seventy-two.

836
00:36:06,980 --> 00:36:07,659
These nectarines...

837
00:36:08,039 --> 00:36:08,559
Yeah.

838
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:10,179
My mom likes fuzzy peaches.

839
00:36:10,420 --> 00:36:11,380
Let me pour them back, okay?

840
00:36:11,739 --> 00:36:12,460
I'll pour them back, sis.

841
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:13,880
Save a bag.

842
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:15,280
Thanks, thanks sis.

843
00:36:32,079 --> 00:36:32,860
You're back.

844
00:36:33,539 --> 00:36:33,960
Bro.

845
00:36:34,219 --> 00:36:35,559
Mom said you weren't coming back.

846
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:37,420
I missed you two, that's all.

847
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:38,380
Where's Mom?

848
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:40,019
She went to Great-Grandma Seven's place.

849
00:36:51,239 --> 00:36:51,719
Second Sis.

850
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:54,440
Big Sis.

851
00:37:07,679 --> 00:37:08,619
Those two in the same car?

852
00:37:09,059 --> 00:37:09,659
Wouldn't they fight?

853
00:37:10,219 --> 00:37:10,619
Bro.

854
00:37:12,179 --> 00:37:12,500
Bro.

855
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:13,260
Bro.

856
00:37:13,679 --> 00:37:14,679
You came back so soon.

857
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,000
With something this big going down,

858
00:37:16,219 --> 00:37:17,059
how could I not come back?

859
00:37:19,039 --> 00:37:19,659
What happened?

860
00:37:19,940 --> 00:37:21,059
